Implement the following plan:

# Plan: Full Quantum Experience — Key Sync Fix + Emotion Polish + Visual Overhaul

## Context
The demo app works but feels generic. Three categories of changes transform it into something that makes users *feel* quantum protection at every touchpoint:
1. **Bug fix**: Importing a wallet doesn't reset the deploy flow
2. **UI cleanup**: Copyable address, remove technical noise, show deployed/balance status
3. **Full quantum experience**: Text + visual animations that reinforce quantum safety at every interaction — from ambient background to celebratory particles

**Current animation stack**: Pure CSS (no libraries). 15+ keyframes in `globals.css`, glass morphism system, `prefers-reduced-motion` support. No canvas or particle effects yet.

---

## Phase 1: CSS Foundation (`globals.css`)

Add all new keyframes and utility classes to `apps/demo/src/app/globals.css`. These are the building blocks every component will use.

### 1a. Background Aurora
Animate the existing `--mesh-gradient` with a 30s slow drift. Glass cards' `backdrop-filter: blur(20px)` diffuses movement into ambient light leaks.

```css
@keyframes aurora-shift {
  0%   { background-position: 0% 50%, 100% 50%, 50% 100%; }
  50%  { background-position: 100% 30%, 0% 70%, 50% 0%; }
  100% { background-position: 0% 50%, 100% 50%, 50% 100%; }
}

/* Update body rule to add background-size + animation */
body {
  background: var(--mesh-gradient), var(--color-falcon-bg);
  background-size: 200% 200%, 200% 200%, 200% 200%, auto;
  animation: aurora-shift 30s ease-in-out infinite;
}
```

### 1b. Shield Breathing (deployed idle state)
Slow 4s emerald glow pulse — the "heartbeat" of a protected account.

```css
@keyframes shield-breathe {
  0%, 100% {
    border-color: rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.08);
    box-shadow: var(--glass-shadow), 0 0 20px -5px rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.05);
  }
  50% {
    border-color: rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.2);
    box-shadow: var(--glass-shadow), 0 0 30px -5px rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.15);
  }
}

.shield-protected { animation: shield-breathe 4s ease-in-out infinite; }
```

### 1c. Node Completion Burst (step dots)
Sonar ping when a step completes — `box-shadow` ring expands and fades.

```css
@keyframes node-complete {
  0%  { box-shadow: 0 0 0 0 rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.4); }
  70% { box-shadow: 0 0 0 10px rgba(16, 185, 129, 0); }
  100% { box-shadow: 0 0 0 10px rgba(16, 185, 129, 0); }
}

.animate-node-complete { animation: node-complete 0.6s ease-out; }
```

### 1d. Energy Flow (deploy pipeline line)
Flowing gradient on the vertical pipeline connector.

```css
@keyframes energy-flow {
  0%   { background-position: 0% 0%; }
  100% { background-position: 0% 200%; }
}

.energy-conduit {
  width: 2px;
  background: linear-gradient(
    180deg,
    var(--color-falcon-success) 0%,
    var(--color-falcon-primary) 40%,
    rgba(99, 102, 241, 0.1) 60%,
    transparent 100%
  );
  background-size: 100% 200%;
  animation: energy-flow 3s linear infinite;
}
```

### 1e. Quantum Scan Line (active step indicator)
Thin cyan glow line sweeps back and forth during active operations.

```css
@keyframes quantum-scan {
  0%, 100% { left: -30%; opacity: 0; }
  10%      { opacity: 0.8; }
  50%      { left: 100%; }
  90%      { opacity: 0.8; }
}

.quantum-scan-line {
  position: absolute;
  width: 30%;
  height: 1px;
  top: 50%;
  background: linear-gradient(90deg, transparent, var(--color-falcon-accent), transparent);
  animation: quantum-scan 2.5s ease-in-out infinite;
  pointer-events: none;
}
```

### 1f. Lattice Dot Activation (keygen visualization)

```css
@keyframes dot-activate {
  0%   { background: rgba(99, 102, 241, 0.05); transform: scale(0.5); }
  50%  { background: rgba(99, 102, 241, 0.8); transform: scale(1.4); }
  100% { background: rgba(99, 102, 241, 0.3); transform: scale(1); }
}
```

### 1g. Status Pulse Dot (quantum-safe indicator)

```css
@keyframes status-pulse {
  0%, 100% { opacity: 0.4; box-shadow: 0 0 0 0 rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.4); }
  50%      { opacity: 1;   box-shadow: 0 0 0 4px rgba(16, 185, 129, 0); }
}

.status-dot-protected {
  display: inline-block;
  width: 6px; height: 6px;
  border-radius: 50%;
  background: var(--color-falcon-success);
  animation: status-pulse 3s ease-in-out infinite;
}
```

### 1h. Shield Draw (SVG stroke animation)

```css
@keyframes shield-draw {
  from { stroke-dashoffset: 80; }
  to   { stroke-dashoffset: 0; }
}

.animate-shield-draw {
  stroke-dasharray: 80;
  animation: shield-draw 0.8s cubic-bezier(0.32, 0.72, 0, 1) forwards;
}
```

### 1i. Check Draw (animated checkmark)

```css
@keyframes check-draw {
  from { stroke-dashoffset: 20; }
  to   { stroke-dashoffset: 0; }
}

.animate-check-draw {
  stroke-dasharray: 20;
  animation: check-draw 0.4s cubic-bezier(0.32, 0.72, 0, 1) forwards;
}
```

### 1j. Pop-In (micro-bounce for step completions)

```css
@keyframes pop-in {
  0%   { transform: scale(0); opacity: 0; }
  60%  { transform: scale(1.15); }
  100% { transform: scale(1); opacity: 1; }
}

.animate-pop-in { animation: pop-in 0.3s cubic-bezier(0.32, 0.72, 0, 1) both; }
```

### 1k. Reduced Motion
Add all new animation classes to the existing `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)` block.

---

## Phase 2: Shield SVG Component

**New file**: `apps/demo/src/components/ui/QuantumShield.tsx`

A reusable SVG shield with lattice dot pattern interior. Three sizes (`sm`, `md`, `lg`). Two modes:
- **`animate`**: Shield draws itself shut via `stroke-dashoffset`, then lattice dots fade in from center outward
- **`static`**: Always visible, optional slow subtle rotation (`60s linear infinite`)

Used in: deployed success card header, send section header, key vault header.

The shield SVG structure:
- `<path>` for shield outline with `animate-shield-draw` class
- `<pattern>` with hex-grid dots (3 dots per cell, offset for honeycomb effect)
- Interior `<rect>` filled with the pattern, fading in after shield draws

---

## Phase 3: Particle Convergence Component

**New file**: `apps/demo/src/components/ui/ParticleBurst.tsx`

Lightweight canvas-based celebration for deploy success. ~80 lines of code.

**API**: `<ParticleBurst trigger={boolean} colors={string[]} />`

When `trigger` flips to `true`:
1. Spawn ~50 small square particles (2-4px) at random positions within 300px radius
2. Particles converge inward toward center over 600ms (cubic ease-in)
3. Brief 100ms hold at center
4. Burst outward over 500ms with fade-out (cubic ease-out)
5. Canvas auto-removes after animation

Colors default to `['#6366f1', '#06b6d4', '#10b981']` (primary, accent, success).

---

## Phase 4: Keygen Lattice Visualization Component

**New file**: `apps/demo/src/components/ui/LatticeGrid.tsx`

A 22x24 CSS grid of tiny dots (~528 dots, ≈512 Falcon coefficients) that light up in concentric waves during key generation.

**API**: `<LatticeGrid active={boolean} />`

When `active`:
- Dots light up from center outward in hexagonal rings
- Each ring activates 40ms after the previous one
- Dot transitions: `falcon-muted/5` → brief `falcon-primary` flash → settle at `falcon-primary/30`
- Total wave duration: ~800ms, then loops

When `!active`:
- All dots dim to baseline `falcon-muted/5`

**Implementation**: CSS `transition-delay` calculated per-dot based on distance from center. No JS animation loop — pure CSS transitions triggered by class toggle.

---

## Phase 5: Entropy Visualization Component

**New file**: `apps/demo/src/components/ui/EntropyStrip.tsx`

A small monospace strip showing rapidly-cycling random hex during keygen.

**API**: `<EntropyStrip active={boolean} />`

When `active`:
- Shows `0xA3F1...B7C2` style random hex, updating every 60ms via `setInterval`
- Subtle monospace styling, low opacity (`text-falcon-accent/30`)

When `!active`: hidden.

---

## Phase 6: Bug Fix + Component Changes

### 6a. Fix deploy ↔ key sync (`AccountDeployFlow.tsx`)

Add `useEffect` watching `packedKey`. When it changes, reset deploy to idle + clear `autoRestoreRan`:

```tsx
// Reset on keypair change (wallet import/generate)
const packedKeyValue = Option.getOrUndefined(packedKey)
useEffect(() => {
  // Skip initial mount
  if (!packedKeyValue) return
  setDeployStep({ step: "idle" })
  setPreparedDeploy(Option.none())
  setBalance(null)
  autoRestoreRan.current = false
}, [packedKeyValue]) // eslint-disable-line react-hooks/exhaustive-deps
```

Note: This must be positioned after the network-change reset effect but before auto-restore, so the auto-restore can re-run with the new key.

### 6b. AccountDeployFlow.tsx — Visual + Text Changes

**Text updates** (quantum emotion):
- "Restoring your wallet..." → "Restoring your quantum-safe wallet..."
- `title="Deploying account..."` → `title="Deploying quantum-safe account..."`
- `subtitle=...` → `subtitle="Falcon-512 post-quantum signature in progress..."`
- `hint=...` → `hint="Quantum-safe verification takes ~30-60s on testnet"`
- "Account Already Deployed" → "Quantum Account Already Deployed"
- "Account Deployed" → "Quantum Account Deployed"
- SR-only liveStatus: "Generating Falcon keypair." → "Generating quantum-safe Falcon keypair."
- SR-only liveStatus: "Deploying account transaction." → "Deploying quantum-safe account."
- SR-only liveStatus: "Account deployed with transaction hash..." → "Quantum account deployed..."
- Add `full` prop to deployed `<AddressDisplay />`

**Visual upgrades**:

1. **Pipeline vertical line** → Replace static `w-px bg-falcon-muted/15` div with `energy-conduit` class. Only animate the portion up to the current active/completed step (use dynamic height or clip).

2. **Step dots** → When a step transitions to complete, apply `animate-node-complete` + `animate-pop-in` to the checkmark circle. Active step dot gets a scan-line overlay inside its container.

3. **Deployed success card** → Add `shield-protected` class for breathing glow. Add `<QuantumShield animate />` in the header. Add `<ParticleBurst trigger={justDeployed} />` overlay. Add `<span className="status-dot-protected" />` next to the address.

4. **Auto-restore spinner** → Add `<QuantumShield size="sm" />` next to "Restoring your quantum-safe wallet..."

### 6c. KeyManagementPanel.tsx — Cleanup + Visual

**Structural changes**:
- Replace title "Key Management" → "Quantum Key Vault" with `<QuantumShield size="sm" />` inline
- Replace inline address `<p>` (lines 357-365) with `<AddressDisplay address={currentAddress} full label="Your Quantum-Protected Address" />`
- Delete NTT Coefficients section (lines 368-384) entirely
- Delete Packed Public Key section (lines 386-404) entirely
- Remove `showNtt`/`showPacked` state variables and `nttCoeffs`/`packedSlots` computed values
- "Replace existing wallet?" → "Replace existing quantum wallet?"
- "Verifying Key (896-byte h polynomial)" → "Quantum-Resistant Verifying Key"

**Deployed/balance indicators**:
When `currentAddress` exists, create a `StarknetService` runtime (same pattern as `AccountDeployFlow`) and query `isDeployed` + `getBalance`. Show:
- Green badge "Deployed" with `status-dot-protected` or gray "Not deployed"
- STRK balance via `<TokenAmount />`

**Visual**:
- Add `<LatticeGrid active={isBusy} />` behind the generate button area during keygen
- Add `<EntropyStrip active={isBusy} />` below the generate button during keygen

### 6d. SignVerifyPanel.tsx — Quantum Labels + Visual

**Text updates**:
- "Sign & Verify" (title) → "Quantum Sign & Verify"
- Button label "Sign & Verify" → "Quantum-Sign & Verify"
- "Signing..." → "Quantum-signing..."
- "Signature valid" → "Quantum-safe signature verified"

**Visual**:
- Add `<QuantumShield size="sm" />` in the title
- Success result card: add `shield-protected` class for breathing glow
- The signing spinner: keep existing `animate-spin-ring` but add an outer ring (second `<circle>` rotating the opposite direction at 1.8s) for an orbital/quantum feel

### 6e. SendTransaction.tsx — Quantum Labels + Visual

**Text updates**:
- "Test Your Falcon Account" → "Test Your Quantum-Safe Account"
- "Send STRK" button → "Quantum-Sign & Send"
- "Transaction Confirmed" → "Quantum-Safe Transaction Confirmed"
- "Sending..." button state → "Quantum-signing..."

**Visual**:
- Add `<QuantumShield size="sm" />` in section title
- Success card: add `shield-protected` class + `<ParticleBurst trigger />` on confirmation

### 6f. TransactionPhases.tsx — Quantum Labels

- "Falcon-512 Signing" → "Quantum Signing (Falcon-512)"
- "signing..." → "quantum-signing..."

---

## Files to Modify/Create

| File | Action |
|------|--------|
| `apps/demo/src/app/globals.css` | Add ~80 lines of new keyframes + utility classes |
| `apps/demo/src/components/ui/QuantumShield.tsx` | **New** — Reusable shield SVG with lattice interior |
| `apps/demo/src/components/ui/ParticleBurst.tsx` | **New** — Canvas particle convergence celebration |
| `apps/demo/src/components/ui/LatticeGrid.tsx` | **New** — CSS grid dot visualization for keygen |
| `apps/demo/src/components/ui/EntropyStrip.tsx` | **New** — Random hex cycling strip |
| `apps/demo/src/components/interactive/AccountDeployFlow.tsx` | Bug fix + text + visual upgrades |
| `apps/demo/src/components/interactive/KeyManagementPanel.tsx` | Cleanup + status + text + visual |
| `apps/demo/src/components/interactive/SignVerifyPanel.tsx` | Text + visual |
| `apps/demo/src/components/interactive/SendTransaction.tsx` | Text + visual |
| `apps/demo/src/components/ui/TransactionPhases.tsx` | Quantum labels |

## Execution Order

1. `globals.css` — CSS foundation (all other changes depend on these classes)
2. `QuantumShield.tsx` — Shared component used everywhere
3. `ParticleBurst.tsx` — Used in deploy success + send success
4. `LatticeGrid.tsx` + `EntropyStrip.tsx` — Used in keygen
5. `AccountDeployFlow.tsx` — Bug fix + largest visual overhaul
6. `KeyManagementPanel.tsx` — Cleanup + status indicators
7. `SignVerifyPanel.tsx` — Text + visual polish
8. `SendTransaction.tsx` + `TransactionPhases.tsx` — Text + visual polish

## Verification
1. Background aurora: slow gradient drift visible behind glass cards
2. Generate wallet → lattice grid lights up, entropy strip cycles, shield icon appears on completion
3. Import wallet B → deploy resets to idle, shows wallet B's address (bug fix confirmed)
4. Address is copyable, NTT/packed sections gone, deployed/balance status shown
5. Deploy pipeline: energy conduit flows, step dots pop + burst on completion
6. Deploy success: particles converge + burst, shield draws itself, card breathes with emerald glow
7. Sign & Verify: orbital spinner during signing, shield-breathing success card
8. Send STRK: "Quantum-Sign & Send", particle burst on confirmation
9. All text says "quantum" at every touchpoint
10. `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce` disables all new animations gracefully


If you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /home/felt/.REDACTED.jsonl

